
                                            Police say the suspects stole an undisclosed amount of cash before fleeing the scene.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Five people have been shot dead and two others injured when a group of heavily armed men opened fire at a shopping complex in KwaDlangezwa near Empangeni in KwaZulu-Natal. It’s alleged that the armed suspects approached the supermarket last night and opened fire at the security guards and customers in the vicinity. Police say the suspects stole an undisclosed amount of cash before fleeing the scene. Security guards and a bystander who was sitting in his vehicle are among those who were killed. The police’s Thulani Zwane: "Police have opened five cases of murder, as well as two cases of attempted murder and business robbery. There have been no arrests at this stage but our acting provincial commissioner Bheki Langa has charged seasoned detectives to investigate these cases."